PROUDLY PRESENTING

AUXILIARY FUEL SYSTEM

Dymech designed and fabricated this auxiliary fuel system for Environment and Climate Change Canada (ECCC). The machine primarily relies on standard automotive components to provide separate adjustable low or high pressure fuel supply systems for carburated and injected small engines undergoing automated service accumulation tests. The system is controlled by customized touchscreen HMI's which display and collect data relating to fuel level, fuel flow rates, and fuel pressures.
